'''左腦解譯器'''(英文：Left-brain interpreter)是由[[心理學家|心理學家]][[邁克爾·葛詹尼加|邁克爾·葛詹尼加]]和[[神經科學家|神經科學家]]約瑟夫·E·勒杜克斯提出的[[神經心理學|神經心理學]]概念。<ref>{{cite book |last1=Gazzaniga |first1=Michael |authorlink1=Michael S. Gazzaniga |last2=Ivry|first2=Richard|authorlink2=RichardIvry|last3=Mangun|first3=George|authorlink3=George Mangun|date=2014|title=Cognitive Neuroscience. The Biology of the Mind. Fourth Edition |pages=153}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |last= Gazzaniga |first= Michael |authorlink= Michael S. Gazzaniga |date=1985 |title= The Social Brain. Discovering the Networks of the Mind |url= https://archive.org/details/socialbraindisco0000gazz |url-access= registration |pages=[https://archive.org/details/socialbraindisco0000gazz/page/5 5]}}</ref>它指的是由[[左腦|左腦]]半球構造解釋，以便通過使新信息與以前已知的信息相協調來了解世界。<ref>''Neurosociology: The Nexus Between Neuroscience and Social Psychology'' by David D. Franks 2010 {{ISBN|1-4419-5530-5}} page 34</ref>左腦解譯器試圖合理化、推理和概括其收到的新信息，以使過去與現在聯繫起來。<ref name=Daniel >''The Seven Sins of Memory: How the Mind Forgets and Remembers'' by Daniel L. Schacter 2002 {{ISBN|0-618-21919-6}} page 159 [https://books.google.com/books?id=m8qMjPF1NYAC&pg=PA159&dq=%22left+brain+interpreter%22+inferences+rationalizations&hl=en&ei=L1-sTpa9M8Xvsgbn3tz1Dw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDEQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22left%20brain%20interpreter%22%20inferences%20rationalizations&f=false] {{Wayback|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=m8qMjPF1NYAC&pg=PA159&dq=%22left+brain+interpreter%22+inferences+rationalizations&hl=en&ei=L1-sTpa9M8Xvsgbn3tz1Dw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=1&ved=0CDEQ6AEwAA#v=onepage&q=%22left%20brain%20interpreter%22%20inferences%20rationalizations&f=false |date=20200114144102 }}</ref>

左腦解譯器是[[腦功能側化|腦功能偏側化]]的一種情況，適用於“解釋生成”而不是其他偏側化活動。<ref name=Gazzaniga >''The cognitive neuroscience of mind: a tribute to Michael S. Gazzaniga'' edited by Patricia A. Reuter-Lorenz, Kathleen Baynes, George R. Mangun, and Elizabeth A. Phelps; The MIT Press; 2010; {{ISBN|0-262-01401-7}}; pages 34-35</ref>儘管左腦解釋器的概念最初是基於對[[裂腦|裂腦]]患者的實驗，但此後已被證明適用於廣大人群的日常行為。<ref name=Gazzaniga />

